│ The `submit-patch` command failed again. The build was successful, but the test case still shows the same miscompilation. This indicates that my previous patch, although syntactically  │
│ correct and placed correctly, did not fix the logical error in the compiler pass.                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Let's re-examine the problem and my previous fix.                                                                                                                                        │
│ The miscompilation happens because `correlated-propagation` incorrectly deduces that the `switch` in `loop3` can be replaced by `unreachable`. This is based on a faulty analysis of the │
│ value of `%phi`.                                                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My previous patch was:                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (FromBB == ToBB) {                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   if (auto *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(V)) {                                                                                                                                                 │
│     if (PN->getParent() == ToBB)                                                                                                                                                         │
│       return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This patch is intended to handle self-edges. It checks if the value `V` is a PHI node residing in the block that has a self-edge (`FromBB == ToBB`). In the test case, the self-edge is  │
│ on `loop3`. The PHI node `%phi` is in the `loop` block. So when `getConstantOnEdge` is called for the `loop3 -> loop3` edge, `ToBB` is `loop3`, but `PN->getParent()` is `loop`. The     │
│ condition `PN->getParent() == ToBB` is false, so my patch has no effect. This explains why it didn't fix the issue.                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is more subtle. The pass is getting confused by the loop structure. The value of `%phi` is `-1` on the first iteration and `0` on subsequent iterations. The pass            │
│ incorrectly assumes it's always `0` when analyzing `loop3`.                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A known fix for a similar issue involves making the analysis of PHI nodes on self-edges more conservative, even if the PHI is not in the self-looping block. The key is that if we are   │
│ on a self-edge (`FromBB == ToBB`), we should not try to resolve the value of *any* PHI node, because its value is established upon entry to the block and is invariant during the        │
│ self-loop. Trying to re-evaluate it can lead to incorrect circular reasoning.                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ So, the correct logic should be: if we are on a self-edge, and we are querying the value of a PHI node, we should just give up.                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The corrected patch should be:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (FromBB == ToBB) {                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   if (isa<PHINode>(V))                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This is a more general and correct check for this situation. It prevents `getConstantOnEdge` from making any assumptions about any PHI node's value on any self-edge.                    │
