│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The issue persists despite my previous attempts. The core problem is that `correlated-propagation` incorrectly determines the value of `%phi` within `loop3`, leading it to believe the  │
│ default case of the switch is unreachable. My previous patches to `LazyValueInfo::getConstantOnEdge` were insufficient.                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The analysis seems to be failing due to the complex interaction of loops and PHI nodes. The pass incorrectly concludes that `%phi` can never be `-1` when execution reaches `loop3`.     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A similar, subtle bug was fixed in LLVM by making the PHI node analysis in `LazyValueInfo` more conservative. Specifically, when analyzing a PHI node, if any of its incoming values are │
│ themselves PHI nodes, the analysis should be aborted for that path. This prevents the solver from entering complex, potentially incorrect, recursive reasoning about chains of PHI       │
│ nodes.                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix involves modifying the `solve` function within `LazyValueInfoCache::getLatticeValueFor`. When iterating through the incoming values of a PHI node, if an incoming value is       │
│ another PHI node, we should immediately stop and return `overdefined`.                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will first revert my previous patch. I inserted 4 lines at line 1842 of `llvm/lib/Analysis/LazyValueInfo.cpp`.                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1842,1845d' llvm/lib/Analysis/LazyValueInfo.cpp                                                                                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
