│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The previous attempts failed, even though the logic seemed plausible. The issue is that the miscompilation persists, indicating my patches were ineffective. I have reverted all         │
│ previous changes.                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The core of the problem lies in how `LazyValueInfo` handles PHI nodes in the presence of self-loops. When `getConstantOnEdge` is called for an edge `B -> B`, it can lead to incorrect   │
│ assumptions if it tries to resolve the value of a PHI node. My previous attempt to fix this was:                                                                                         │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (FromBB == ToBB) {                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   if (isa<PHINode>(V))                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This seems correct, but it failed. It's possible that the context of the call matters. The `getConstantOnEdge` function takes a context instruction `CxtI`. A known fix for a very       │
│ similar bug involves checking if the context instruction is within the block that has the self-loop. If we are trying to determine a PHI's value on a self-edge, and the query           │
│ originates from within that same block, it can lead to circular reasoning.                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct fix is likely a more refined version of my previous attempt. It should check not only for a self-edge (`FromBB == ToBB`) and a PHI node (`isa<PHINode>(V)`), but also ensure │
│ that the context instruction `CxtI` is inside the block with the self-loop.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The refined patch is:                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (FromBB == ToBB && CxtI && CxtI->getParent() == FromBB) {                                                                                                                             │
│   if (isa<PHINode>(V))                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This is more precise. It only disables PHI analysis on self-edges when the query itself originates from an instruction within the looping block, which is the exact scenario that causes │
│ the faulty circular reasoning.                                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will apply this patch to `llvm/lib/Analysis/LazyValueInfo.cpp` at line 1842, which is the start of the `getConstantOnEdge` function body.                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1842i\                                                                                                                                                                           │
│   if (FromBB == ToBB && CxtI && CxtI->getParent() == FromBB) {\                                                                                                                          │
│     if (isa<PHINode>(V))\                                                                                                                                                                │
│       return nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   }\                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ' llvm/lib/Analysis/LazyValueInfo.cpp                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
