│ which means the root cause is more subtle than my previous analyses have captured.                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is that `LazyValueInfo` provides incorrect information to `correlated-propagation`. The analysis incorrectly concludes that the PHI node `%phi` can never be `-1` when the   │
│ `switch` in `loop3` is executed. This is due to the complex loop structure, particularly the self-loop on `loop3`.                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will make one final attempt based on a known fix for a very similar bug (LLVM PR21688). This fix is more specific than my previous attempts. It targets the exact condition that leads │
│ to faulty circular reasoning: querying the value of a PHI node on a self-edge (`B -> B`) where the query itself originates from an instruction within block `B`.                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The patch is to be added at the beginning of `LazyValueInfo::getConstantOnEdge`:                                                                                                         │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (FromBB == ToBB && CxtI && CxtI->getParent() == FromBB)                                                                                                                               │
│   if (isa<PHINode>(V))                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This is my most precise attempt yet. It constrains the conservative behavior to the exact problematic scenario.                                                                          │
